nd cinematic histories that go beyond a film's plot to index, circulate, and reproduce broader narratives about Black sporting and non-sporting experiences in American society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAfrican Americans in motion pictures. 0aRace in motion pictures. 0aSports in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aa league of their own.  aafrican american studies.  aafrican american.  aathletes.  abasketball.  ablack athletes.  ablack body.  ablack women.  ablackness.  aboobie miles.  aethnic studies.  afemale athletes.  afilm.  afootball.  afriday night lights.  agender studies.  ahoop dreams.  ahoop reality.  ahour glass.  ajames miles.  ajuwanna mann.  alove and basketball.  amedia studies.  aolympic protest.  aolympics.  apopular culture.  apro athletes.  arace.  aracial representation.  aracism.  aresistance.  asports documentaries.  asports films.  asports icon.  asports movies.  atommie smith.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520973855zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520973855423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520973855.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 20